Member Enumeration Documentation

enum InterfaceRequest::state_t
 

The states of an InterfaceRequest.

Enumeration values:
Ready_To_IO_Request  Ready to do IO for receiving request.
Ready_To_IO_Reply  Ready to do IO for sending reply.
Ready_To_Process  Has a complete request that is ready to be processed.
Done  Done, all done.
Error  Error, something went wrong.
Timeout_request  Timeout on IO when receiving request.
Timeout_reply  Timeout on IO when sending reply.
Uninitalized  Not yet initialized.

virtual void InterfaceRequest::terminate (   )  [virtual]
 

The irequest should try to get done as soon as possible.

This means that reuse of IO for another read of user request is not wanted. Default is to do nothing.

Reimplemented in HttpInterfaceRequest, IsabBoxInterfaceRequest, SelectableInterfaceRequest, and SendDataInterfaceRequest.
